cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about a toolkit for text generation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses issues related to model development and evaluation, which are common topics in machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. Additionally, the paper mentions metrics and benchmark models, which are often used in neural networks (NN) and deep learning (DL), making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses text generation evaluation, which is related to information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a less likely but still possible category.
